As of the 2010 census, there were 96 people living in the CDP: 47 male and 49 female. 40 were 19 years old or younger, 24 were ages 20–34, 12 were between the ages of 35 and 49, 15 were between 50 and 64, and the remaining 5 were aged 65 and above. The median age was 26 years.

The racial makeup of the CDP was 99% [[Race (United States Census)|American Indian]], and 1% [[Race (United States Census)|two or more races]].  1% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

There were 26 households in the CDP, 17 family households (65%) and 9 non-family households (35%), with an average household size of 3.7. Of the family households, 2 were married couples living together, 4 were single fathers, and 11 were single mothers; the non-family households included 6 adults living alone: 3 male and 3 female.

The CDP contained 39 housing units, of which 26 were occupied and 13 were vacant.<ref name=GR2>{{cite web |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0430850 |title=American FactFinder: Haivana Nakya CDP, Arizona |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=November 23, 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213063233/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0430850 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 }}</ref>

